The paper deals with a hypothesis testing problem in which data is compressed distributively and sent to a detector. This problem is related to distributed source coding, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of random binning, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of encoding rates and error probabilities, which is a common theme in distributed systems (cs.DS) and multimedia (cs.MM).
